A mother of two from Kimilili town in Bungoma county is nursing serious injuries after her husband assaulted her for asking him for money.Iriz Atieno was on Saturday assaulted by Denis Wafula, who knocked out her three upper teeth and nearly gouged out her right eye. Wafula works as a welder in Kimilili town.She needed the money for food and treating their two-year-old child.They have been married for six years. &ldquo;Residents tried to help but he said he is disciplining me,&rdquo; Atieno said. Speaking at her house yesterday, Atieno said she was treated and discharged from Dreamland Hospital. Doctors said she has lost sight in the injured eye.She urged Bungoma county commissioner Joshua Chepchieg to intervene and have her husband arrested.